leetcode:- 19. Remove Nth Node From End of List

ques:-
Given the head of a linked list, remove the nth node from the end of the list and return its head.

note(imp):-
1. dummy is use to hande edge cases, like when we have to remove head.
2. in the case , when list is empty:-

Step 3: Move fast (n+1 times = 2 times)
Move 1: fast = NULL
Move 2: ❌ fast = fast->next (invalid)

⚠️ Important
LeetCode guarantees:

1 ≤ n ≤ length of list

Since length = 0, this case will NOT be tested.

approach:-

class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeNthFromEnd(ListNode* head, int n) {
        ListNode* dummy=new ListNode(0);
        dummy->next=head;
        ListNode* slow=dummy;
        ListNode* fast=dummy;
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            fast=fast->next;
        }
        while(fast!=NULL){
            slow=slow->next;
            fast=fast->next;
        }
        slow->next=slow->next->next;
        return dummy->next;
    }
};
